article.headline: Lipscomb 70, SE Louisiana 58
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Three players scored in double figures in Lipscomb's 70-58 win against Southeastern Louisiana on Thursday night. Adnan Hodzic led the way scoring 16 points off the bench, followed by Michael Lusk with 15 and Josh Slater with 11. Brandon Brown had a game-high 10 rebounds for the Bisons (2-1). Lipscomb out rebounded Southeastern Louisiana (1-2) by a count of 40-17. Lipscomb had 10 steals, while Josh Slater, Brandon Brown and Lusk had two each. The Bisons made half of their shots, connecting on 24 of 48 field goals. Kevyn Green led Southeastern Louisiana and all scorers at 26 points. Patrick Sullivan contributed four blocks for the Lions.
